From Ma et al: "HD 26965 is the primary of a very widely separated triple system. The  other two companions are an M4 dwarf and a white dwarf. The on-sky separation between the primary and the other two stars is about 82 arcsec. The estimated orbital period of this system is ∼8000 yr (Heintz 1974). This star has a star-spot activity cycle period of 10.1 yr (Baliunas et al. 1995)."
